/-!
# Cyclic Base Change

Let $E/F$ be a finite solvable extension of totally real fields of even degree,
let $p>2$ be a prime and let $\rho : \text{Gal}(F^\bar/F) \to \text{GL}_2(\mathbb{Q}_p^\bar)$ be a continuous representation,
which is irreducible even when restricted to $\text{Gal}(E^\bar/E)$. Let $S$ be a finite
set of finite places of $F$, not dividing $p$.

Suppose furthermore
* $\rho$ unramified outside $S$ and $p$;
* $\rho$ descends to $\rho_0 : \text{Gal}(F^\bar/F) \to \text{GL}_2(R)$ with $R \subseteq \mathbb{Q}_p^\bar$ a subring finite
  free over $\mathbb{Z}_p$, and $\rho_0$ is flat at all places of $F$ dividing $p$;
* If $v \in S$ then the restriction of $\rho$ to $F_v$ has a rank one tame quotient;
* $\det(\rho)$ is the cyclotomic character.

Then $\rho$ is automorphic of level $U_1(S)$ iff $\rho|_E$ is automorphic of level $U_1(S_E)$,
where $S_E$ is the pullback of $S$ to $E$.
-/

