  -- This is a fundamental theorem in the theory of automorphic forms and
  -- their associated Galois representations, often referred to as the
  -- "cyclic base change" or "ramification" theorem. It states that if a
  -- 2-dimensional p-adic Galois representation ρ of a totally real
  -- number field F of even degree is automorphic of level S, then its
  -- restriction to a finite solvable extension E/F is automorphic of
  -- level S_E, where S_E is the preimage of S under the natural map E → F.
  -- The converse also holds.
  -- The proof involves showing that the local conditions at primes not
  -- dividing p are automatically satisfied because the representations
  -- are unramified outside S and p. The main work is to show that the
  -- existence of an automorphic form for ρ implies the existence of a
  -- corresponding form for ρ|_E and vice versa.
